 <div class="column" style="background-color:lightgrey;height: 480px; padding-right:2%">
   <h2 style="text-align:center">Encryption </h2>
   <p style="font-size: 20px; text-align:center" >Encryption is the process of converting information into a cipher or a code so that it cannot be readable to all other people except those who hold a key for the cipher text. The cipher text or encoded text is called as encrypted data.
<p style="text-align:center">State of databases protection :</p>
<ul style="text-align:center">1. At Rest – data may be stored in a database or in backend tape  </ul>
<ul style="text-align:center">2. At Transit – data travelling across the network which dictates different encryption solutions for the data in transit. </ul>
<!--<ul style="text-align:center">3. Data rights - right to retrieve or update information in a database.  </ul>-->
</p>

